223505273.body:
$TSLA     We are looking at a few things here: 
 
1) q2 < 100K. Not a growth story. Next week we know how bad things really are.  Nobody cares what WS expectation is. They can artificially lower it to look like a beat. No reason to consider anything below 100K as a success since current valuation assumes high growth for 5 years. 
 
2) Rotation of funds into bonds. https://www.marketwatch.com/story/7-reasons-the-stock-market-may-face-a-severe-bout-of-turbulence-next-week-and-beyondonly-one-is-rising-coronavirus-cases-2020-06-27 It will be dark without the print press. 
 
3) competition entering EV space with a bang. 
 
4) Tesla quality control issues mainly due to production scaling rush.   
 
5) lawsuits pending against Tesla. 
 
6) COVID situation is worsening. We might be looking at another factories closures this year. 
 
The price is already expensive. The high growth story is fake. 
 
Selling now and looking for a better entry is a sensible strategy in these uncertain times. Play it smart.
